## 10. Mobile OTP Auth (`mobile-otp-auth.tsx`)

Inline 3-step flow (no page redirect): Mobile input → OTP input → Success. Calls `/api/auth/otp/send` and `/api/auth/otp/verify`. On success, calls `router.refresh()` to pick up new session. Shows "+91" prefix, 30s resend countdown, handles new vs returning user messaging.

---

## 11. OTP Auth Backend

### `/api/auth/otp/send`
- Validates Indian mobile (starts 6-9, 10 digits)
- MOCK: generates random 6-digit OTP, logs to console in dev
- TODO: Replace with MSG91/Twilio

### `/api/auth/otp/verify`
- MOCK: accepts any 6-digit code
- Maps mobile to email: `{mobile}@pranajiva.in`
- Derives deterministic password: `CF_{mobile}_{salt_prefix}` (uses `OTP_PASSWORD_SALT` env var)
- Tries `medusaClient.auth.getToken()` first (existing customer)
- If fails, creates customer via `medusaClient.customers.create()` then gets token
- Sets `_medusa_jwt` cookie (7 days, httpOnly, strict, secure in prod)
- Returns `{ success: true, isNewUser: boolean }`

