## 25. Multi-Storefront Architecture (Frontend Perspective)
Single Codebase, Two Domains
The same Next.js 14 application is deployed to serve both storefronts:



Domain	Brand	What's Shown
crossfriend.in	CrossFriend	Cakes, Decor, Gifts, Costumes, AI Cake Studio
pranajiva.in	PranaJiva	Ayurvedic & Wellness products
How Brand Differentiation Works
Product/Collection/Category filtering: All data-layer queries in src/lib/data/index.ts filter by metadata.brand = "crossfriend". PranaJiva storefront filters by metadata.brand = "pranajiva".
Feature gating: The frontend decides which pages/features are accessible on which domain. AI Cake Studio is only shown on crossfriend.in.
Backend is brand-agnostic: The Medusa backend serves all data without brand filtering. Filtering is purely a frontend responsibility.
AI Cake Studio — Frontend's Responsibility
The frontend is responsible for:

Showing AI Cake Studio only on crossfriend.in (not on pranajiva.in)
Calling backend APIs (/store/ai-studio/generate, /store/ai-studio/credits, etc.) — these are brand-agnostic endpoints
Displaying results with CrossFriend branding (violet theme, CrossFriend messaging)
Gating access — the "Login to Generate" flow, attempts badge, exhausted state
NOT sending any brand identifier to the backend — backend doesn't need it
What Backend Provides (Brand-Agnostic)
The backend exposes generic task-specific APIs:



Endpoint	What It Does	Frontend's Job
POST /store/ai-studio/generate	Generates cake images for any authenticated customer	Only call this from CrossFriend's AI Cake Studio page
GET /store/ai-studio/credits	Returns credit balance for any customer	Only show this on CrossFriend
GET /store/ai-studio/history	Returns generation history for any customer	Only show this on CrossFriend
POST /store/ai-studio/leads	Creates a baker lead for any customer	Only trigger from CrossFriend's baker flow
Customer Accounts
Shared across brands. A customer who signs up via OTP on crossfriend.in has the same Medusa customer record as if they logged in on pranajiva.in.
Credits are per-customer, not per-brand. If a customer has 3 free AI generations, that's their balance regardless of which domain they're on.
Frontend prevents cross-brand access by simply not showing the AI Cake Studio UI on pranajiva.in.
Future: PranaJiva AI Chatbot
Will be a separate set of frontend components (not AI Cake Studio)
Will call different backend endpoints (e.g., /store/ai-chatbot/ask)
Will only be shown on pranajiva.in
Backend will have a separate service (ai-chatbot.ts) specialized for Ayurvedic text Q&A
Same infrastructure: Redis, PostgreSQL, same Medusa customer auth
